      • and

        public static <T> Predicate<T> and(Predicate<? super T>... components)
        Returns a Predicate that evaluates to true iff each of its components evaluates to true. The components are evaluated in order, and evaluation will be "short-circuited" as soon as the answer is determined. Does not defensively copy the array passed in, so future changes to it will alter the behavior of this Predicate.

        public static <T> Predicate<T> or(Predicate<? super T>... components)

The components are evaluated in order, and evaluation will be "short-circuited" as soon as the answer is determined. Does not defensively copy the array passed in, so future changes to it will alter the behavior of this Predicate.
